        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 3:18AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 317 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Niota, or near Fort Madison, moving northeast at 75 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Carman around 325 AM CDT.
Stronghurst around 330 AM CDT.
Biggsville around 335 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
